Use the curl command to download the key and then store it in a safe place by using the following command : 
curl -fsSL https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo
tee /usr/share/keyrings/kubernetes.gpg

To add Kubernetes repository to the list, execute the following command : 
echo "deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/kubernetes.gpg]
http://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main" | sudo tee -a
/etc/apt/sources.list
